definition: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet/Colors of the rainbow
pinyin: hong2 cheng2 huang2 lu:4 lan2 dian4 zi3

sentences.english: It produces round, light orange-colored fruits about the size of lemons.
sentences.chinese: 它的果实是圆形的，淡橙黄色，和柠檬一般大小。

sentences.english: I had my hair dyed orange.
The contrast of white and orange was so beautiful!
sentences.chinese: 显然白雪和橙黄色的对比是很美丽的。

sentences.english: His comb was as red as fire, and his feathers were as yellow as gold.
sentences.chinese: 他的鸡冠鲜红似火，羽毛橙黄如金。

sentences.english: Afternoon sun, relaxing and warm the heart of Orange lit.
sentences.chinese: 午后的阳光，暖洋洋的照得内心橙黄。

sentences.english: The plant has a beautiful orange flower, which blooms in May every year.
sentences.chinese: 这种植物有着美丽的橙黄色的花，在每年的五月绽放。

sentences.english: In fact, however, Orange Pekoe has nothing at all to do with the tea's flavor.
sentences.chinese: 但事实上，橙黄白毫已经什么都做与茶的味道。

sentences.english: The tiny orange bird just lay there.
sentences.chinese: 这只橙黄色的小鸟躺在那儿一动不动。

sentences.english: The designer has chosen the complementary colours blue and orange.
sentences.chinese: 设计师选取了蓝和橙黄两种对比色。

sentences.english: Old World alpine poppy with white or yellow to orange flowers.
sentences.chinese: 东半球一种山罂粟，开白或黄到橙黄色花。
